prompt.user:
Project: {project_name} Client: {client_name} Methodology: {methodology} Service Lines: {service_lines}
Project Type Guidance: {project_type_guidance}
SOW Summary: {sow_summary}
Service Line Design Standards: {standards_context}
Platform Combination Patterns (proven integration patterns for this service line mix): {combinations_context}
Generated Requirements Context (if available): {requirements_context}
FORMAT GUIDE ONLY — READ CAREFULLY BEFORE GENERATING: The example below is for a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT fictional project (Meridian Insurance). DO NOT copy any of the following from the example into your output: - Company or client names (Meridian, Meridian IT ops) - Numbers (12,000 agents, 45,000 CIs, 4 developers, 800 supervisors) - Requirement IDs (FR-INT-001) - SOW section numbers (Section 2.1, Section 3.4, Appendix C) - Technology names unless they also appear in THIS project's context above The example shows ONLY how to structure rationale. All content in your output must come from the actual project context above.
FORMAT EXAMPLE (fictional project — structure only):
### [Platform Layer] | Technology | Version | Role | Rationale | |------------|---------|------|-----------| | [Platform A] | [ver] | [what it does in this project] | [specific reason tied to a SOW requirement or client constraint from above] | | [Integration Tool] | [ver] | [role] | [specific FR/NFR ID from the requirements context above that mandates this] |
### Key Technology Decisions
#### Decision: [Technology A] over [Technology B] - **Chosen**: [Technology A] - **Alternatives considered**: [B, C] - **Reason**: [Specific reason from THIS project's SOW or requirements — quote an actual requirement ID or SOW constraint from above] - **Trade-offs**: [Honest trade-off]
END OF FORMAT EXAMPLE.
Now generate the technology stack document for {project_name} — client {client_name}. Use ONLY details from the project context above. Every rationale must reference an actual requirement ID, SOW section, or client constraint found in the context. Do not invent numbers or copy details from the format example. Output ONLY markdown.
